# Excalibur Training Day Log — Activity Order

When editing Tacie's Training Directives (day cards with AM/PM activities):

**Always list AIS (Activation) before the Run** when both appear on the same day.

- **AIS** = Active Isolated Stretching routines (e.g. "AIS Routine 1: The Rope", "AIS Routine 2: The Matrix", or links to `tacie_ais_4kL9m.html`, `tacie_mobility_5nB8v.html`).
- **Run** = Any run prescription (e.g. "3 Miles Zone 2", "4 Miles Fartlek/Threshold").

Correct order in the day card: **Activation / AIS first**, then **Run**, then any Chassis/Circuit or other work.

### Example (correct)

```html
<div class="activity">Activation: <a href="tacie_ais_4kL9m.html" ...>AIS Routine 1: The Rope</a>.</div>
<div class="activity"><strong>Run:</strong> 3 Miles (Zone 2).</div>
```

### Example (wrong — Run before AIS)

```html
<div class="activity"><strong>Run:</strong> 3 Miles (Zone 2).</div>
<div class="activity">Activation: <a href="tacie_ais_4kL9m.html" ...>AIS Routine 1: The Rope</a>.</div>
```

If the day has only a run (no AIS), no change. If the day has AIS + run, ensure AIS appears first in the markup.

